The soldier who had identified himself as Tankor turned a cold optic
on Hydras, seemingly devoid of anything approaching mercy or empathy,
instead there was just the remorseless gaze of a soldier and
destroyer, &quot;You are to be taken to the city and brought before
Breakout.&quot; Tankor said simply, &quot;If this is to be an escort of your
troops or the transport of spare parts, the choice is yours.&quot;

&quot;How dare you talk to the royalty that way!&quot; Inferno said as he
stepped foward boldly, ready to face down anyone who challenged
Hydras. The other Predacons looked ready to fight as well.

Meanwhile the other soldiers that had come with Tankor were silent and
motionless, looking little more than drone waiting for his command.
Yet their large weapon mounts were mute testimony as to what would
happen should Hydras refuse to comply or his soldiers choose to fight.

Tankor&#39;s ignored Inferno as he watched Hydras, although one of the
other tanks reoriented its weapon to cover Inferno.

